WEBVTT

1
00:00:07.507 --> 00:00:10.010
[Rafelet babbling]

2
00:00:15.473 --> 00:00:17.142
[indistinct chatter]

3
00:00:19.019 --> 00:00:21.896
[María laughing]

4
00:00:22.856 --> 00:00:24.607
[María] Oh…

5
00:00:24.691 --> 00:00:26.401
- It's over.
- [Rafelet] Papa!

6
00:00:26.484 --> 00:00:28.778
[Benito] Say. "Dad.
I think Mom's leaving."

7
00:00:29.612 --> 00:00:30.572
Come here. come on.

8
00:00:30.655 --> 00:00:32.198
- Papa.
- [Benito] Go to Dad. go.

9
00:00:32.282 --> 00:00:33.324
Papa!

10
00:00:33.408 --> 00:00:34.659
Aye! Aye! Aye!

11
00:00:34.743 --> 00:00:36.745
[peaceful music playing]

12
00:00:39.414 --> 00:00:41.916
- [Rafa] Bye. Rafelet! Bye-bye.
- [Benito] Say. "You got this."

13
00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:44.252
- [Mwah]
- [María] Yay!

14
00:00:48.631 --> 00:00:51.676
[commentator] <i>Everything's been sold out</i>
<i>for days. almost a week.</i>

15
00:00:51.760 --> 00:00:55.388
<i>That's because no one wants to miss</i>
<i>not just a Rafa Nadal match.</i>

16
00:00:55.472 --> 00:00:57.557
<i>but seeing Rafa Nadal in person.</i>

17
00:00:58.058 --> 00:00:59.851
[Marc] Lots of people today.

18
00:01:00.769 --> 00:01:04.230
[fans shouting] Rafa! Rafa!

19
00:01:04.314 --> 00:01:06.441
[interviewer] <i>What'd you like</i>
<i>to see happen in Madrid</i>

20
00:01:06.524 --> 00:01:09.527
<i>in your comeback process</i>
<i>and preparation for Roland-Garros?</i>

21
00:01:10.779 --> 00:01:13.114
[Rafa] <i>For me. Roland-Garros is</i>

22
00:01:13.198 --> 00:01:16.326
the most important tournament
of my tennis career.

23
00:01:16.409 --> 00:01:20.497
So. the next couple of weeks
are so important to…

24
00:01:20.997 --> 00:01:24.417
to see if that's
a real possibility or not.

25
00:01:27.337 --> 00:01:29.380
[indistinct chatter]

26
00:01:29.464 --> 00:01:31.216
- [Moyá] Stay positive.
- Yeah.

27
00:01:31.299 --> 00:01:34.135
It's impossible to go from 0
just sitting to suddenly 100.

28
00:01:34.969 --> 00:01:37.388
But you're getting there. It's possible.

29
00:01:38.264 --> 00:01:39.974
[music fades]

30
00:01:41.184 --> 00:01:43.603
[Marc] This guy…
he doesn't know what's coming.

31
00:01:43.686 --> 00:01:44.771
[toilet flushes]

32
00:01:45.855 --> 00:01:47.190
[indistinct chatter]

33
00:01:55.865 --> 00:01:58.201
- [door closes]
- [toilet flushes]

34
00:01:59.119 --> 00:02:00.912
[Marc] How many times is he gonna pee?

35
00:02:02.080 --> 00:02:04.082
[Maymó] I don't know
if it's nerves or what.

36
00:02:04.165 --> 00:02:06.042
[toilet flushes]

37
00:02:07.252 --> 00:02:10.672
- [Rafa] The toilet's outta water.
- [all laugh]

38
00:02:14.175 --> 00:02:15.635
Come on. man. Let's go.

39
00:02:15.718 --> 00:02:18.096
[inspirational music playing]

40
00:02:24.227 --> 00:02:28.231
[commentator] <i>Rafa trained this morning.</i>
<i>getting ready for a complicated match.</i>

41
00:02:28.314 --> 00:02:31.442
[commentator 2] <i>He faces Alex de Miñaur.</i>
<i>number 11 in the world.</i>

42
00:02:32.318 --> 00:02:34.529
[commentator 3]
<i>What chance do we give Rafa today?</i>

43
00:02:34.612 --> 00:02:36.573
[commentator 4]
<i>I think a low percentage chance.</i>

44
00:02:36.656 --> 00:02:38.324
<i>If you're Nadal. in the back of your mind.</i>

45
00:02:38.408 --> 00:02:42.036
<i>you're scared that</i>
<i>you might just re-injure yourself.</i>

46
00:02:43.454 --> 00:02:45.039
[shutters clicking]

47
00:02:46.958 --> 00:02:48.459
[Rafa] <i>I ended up giving my life</i>

48
00:02:48.543 --> 00:02:52.046
<i>to one of the most</i>
<i>individual sports that exists.</i>

49
00:02:54.841 --> 00:02:58.678
<i>A sport that creates pressure and stress.</i>

50
00:03:01.306 --> 00:03:04.225
<i>You feel nervous. The nerves are real.</i>

51
00:03:05.393 --> 00:03:07.520
<i>That's why. throughout my career.</i>

52
00:03:08.021 --> 00:03:10.982
<i>my routines helped me a lot</i>
<i>to cope with all that.</i>

53
00:03:11.608 --> 00:03:12.650
[crowd cheering]

54
00:03:19.282 --> 00:03:20.867
[Rafa] <i>It was usually…</i>

55
00:03:21.951 --> 00:03:22.952
<i>pants…</i>

56
00:03:23.870 --> 00:03:28.291
this. this. this. this. this. this.

57
00:03:28.875 --> 00:03:30.835
<i>this. this. this…</i>

58
00:03:31.836 --> 00:03:32.712
and this.

59
00:03:34.005 --> 00:03:37.133
<i>During the game.</i>
<i>I would avoid stepping on the lines.</i>

60
00:03:39.093 --> 00:03:40.678
<i>And on clay courts.</i>

61
00:03:40.762 --> 00:03:43.348
<i>I'd sweep the lines</i>
<i>at the beginning of each game</i>

62
00:03:44.265 --> 00:03:46.434
and. then. at break points.

63
00:03:49.687 --> 00:03:53.650
<i>It was a way to shut myself off</i>
<i>from everything around me.</i>

64
00:03:56.527 --> 00:03:58.238
[fan] Come on. Rafa!

65
00:03:59.489 --> 00:04:01.407
[Rafa] <i>I'm in control when I do them.</i>

66
00:04:03.743 --> 00:04:05.203
[inspirational music builds]

67
00:04:07.163 --> 00:04:10.124
[commentator 5] <i>A win today</i>
<i>could make the tennis world take note.</i>

68
00:04:10.208 --> 00:04:11.584
Come on!

69
00:04:11.668 --> 00:04:14.003
[commentator 5]
<i>Rafa is here to seriously play.</i>

70
00:04:14.963 --> 00:04:16.923
[commentator 6] <i>This is vintage stuff.</i>

71
00:04:17.757 --> 00:04:20.301
[commentator 7]
<i>Fabulous ball striking from Nadal.</i>

72
00:04:21.094 --> 00:04:24.681
[Rafa] <i>To have that feeling you get</i>
<i>by competing at the highest level.</i>

73
00:04:24.764 --> 00:04:27.558
[commentator 6] <i>It's the same amount</i>
<i>of potency as we're used to seeing.</i>

74
00:04:27.642 --> 00:04:30.311
[Rafa] <i>To have the confidence</i>
<i>that I'm going to win.</i>

75
00:04:31.354 --> 00:04:33.648
<i>That feeling in your stomach.</i>

76
00:04:34.148 --> 00:04:35.942
[commentator 7] <i>Nadal. a game away.</i>

77
00:04:36.567 --> 00:04:39.988
[Rafa] <i>You wonder.</i>
<i>"How long can I hold on to this feeling?"</i>

78
00:04:40.738 --> 00:04:44.075
[umpire] Game. set. and match. Nadal.

79
00:04:44.575 --> 00:04:49.914
[commentator 7] <i>It's an enormous win</i>
<i>for Rafael Nadal's 2024 campaign.</i>

80
00:04:50.915 --> 00:04:53.960
[Rafa] <i>Because you know</i>
<i>this feeling won't last forever.</i>

81
00:04:54.460 --> 00:05:00.049
[fans chanting] Rafa! Rafa! Rafa!

82
00:05:00.133 --> 00:05:01.551
Rafa!

83
00:05:01.634 --> 00:05:03.553
[cheering in distance]

84
00:05:03.636 --> 00:05:07.056
- [Rafelet squeals]
- [man in Spanish] Let's go! Very good!

85
00:05:09.684 --> 00:05:11.102
[distant screaming]

86
00:05:11.185 --> 00:05:12.437
[indistinct chatter]

87
00:05:13.688 --> 00:05:15.523
[Marc in English] The bulldozer is back.

88
00:05:16.065 --> 00:05:17.233
[laughter]

89
00:05:18.359 --> 00:05:20.820
[Marc] I hadn't seen you play like that
in a long time. man.

90
00:05:21.571 --> 00:05:22.613
Seriously.

91
00:05:23.406 --> 00:05:25.575
[Carlos] Anyway.
you played really well today.

92
00:05:26.117 --> 00:05:27.368
You used to run a lot more.

93
00:05:27.869 --> 00:05:30.663
- [Rafa] If you say so.
- [Carlos] I'm not saying it. I saw it.

94
00:05:32.457 --> 00:05:33.833
[Maymó] It's good to do a little.

95
00:05:33.916 --> 00:05:36.085
You didn't strain yourself much.
but still.

96
00:05:36.169 --> 00:05:37.754
[Rafa] Okay. but I feel fine.

97
00:05:37.837 --> 00:05:40.506
[Maymó] Okay.
but do at least five minutes. just five.

98
00:05:40.590 --> 00:05:41.841
While you drink that.

99
00:05:42.342 --> 00:05:44.093
[light instrumental music playing]

100
00:05:46.763 --> 00:05:50.141
{\an8}[Moyá] <i>Being here</i>
<i>and seeing him competitive and happy.</i>

101
00:05:51.768 --> 00:05:53.644
{\an8}<i>for me. is a win.</i>

102
00:05:55.396 --> 00:05:57.565
<i>He needs that confidence because…</i>

103
00:05:58.399 --> 00:06:01.569
<i>everything depends on him</i>
<i>believing that he can win.</i>

104
00:06:02.236 --> 00:06:03.988
[distant applause]

105
00:06:05.073 --> 00:06:07.200
[announcer] …his opponent. from Spain.

106
00:06:07.283 --> 00:06:09.035
Rafael Nadal!

107
00:06:09.118 --> 00:06:10.787
[crowd cheering]

108
00:06:10.870 --> 00:06:12.955
[commentator] <i>So much at stake here.</i>

109
00:06:14.123 --> 00:06:15.958
<i>Federer. desperate.</i>

110
00:06:16.042 --> 00:06:19.629
<i>Having lost to Nadal last year on clay.</i>
<i>lost to him on grass.</i>

111
00:06:19.712 --> 00:06:22.757
<i>now he certainly doesn't want</i>
<i>to lose to him on hard courts.</i>

112
00:06:22.840 --> 00:06:24.425
[tense music playing]

113
00:06:24.509 --> 00:06:27.512
{\an8}It was one of the greatest matches
we played against each other.

114
00:06:32.100 --> 00:06:33.726
[commentator] <i>Federer's gotta be thinking.</i>

115
00:06:33.810 --> 00:06:36.979
<i>"What do I have to do</i>
<i>to put this guy away?"</i>

116
00:06:37.647 --> 00:06:38.773
[Roger] <i>Rafa was</i>

117
00:06:39.273 --> 00:06:40.942
just at the absolute peak.

118
00:06:45.613 --> 00:06:46.781
Come on!

119
00:06:47.281 --> 00:06:49.700
[commentator 1]
<i>Rafael Nadal wins in Melbourne</i>

120
00:06:49.784 --> 00:06:52.203
<i>at the Australian Open.</i>
<i>for the first time.</i>

121
00:06:53.204 --> 00:06:55.998
[commentator 2] <i>Rafa Nadal</i>
<i>is the new number 1 in the world.</i>

122
00:06:56.082 --> 00:06:58.501
<i>The Federer era is over.</i>

123
00:06:58.584 --> 00:07:00.169
[dynamic martial music playing]

124
00:07:03.881 --> 00:07:07.176
[commentator 3] <i>He does things</i>
<i>on the court that nobody else could do.</i>

125
00:07:12.890 --> 00:07:15.601
[commentator 4] <i>The new champion.</i>
<i>Rafael Nadal!</i>

126
00:07:16.102 --> 00:07:19.814
[announcer]
The invincible man. Rafa Nadal!

127
00:07:21.149 --> 00:07:23.776
[Wertheim]
<i>2010 is. in some ways. prime Rafa.</i>

128
00:07:23.860 --> 00:07:25.111
<i>He wins at Roland-Garros.</i>

129
00:07:25.945 --> 00:07:28.698
<i>Ends up winning his second Wimbledon.</i>

130
00:07:29.699 --> 00:07:31.701
{\an8}And I remember the discussion shifts.

131
00:07:31.784 --> 00:07:34.412
{\an8}We were all seduced by Roger Federer. but…

132
00:07:34.495 --> 00:07:39.250
"Holy shit! Maybe this
is the greatest player that ever lived."

133
00:07:39.333 --> 00:07:41.335
[dynamic upbeat music playing]

134
00:07:42.628 --> 00:07:46.048
[commentator 1] <i>Rafael Nadal is</i>
<i>the top-ranked tennis player in the world.</i>

135
00:07:47.008 --> 00:07:48.551
<i>He's in New York for the US Open.</i>

136
00:07:48.634 --> 00:07:52.096
<i>the only major tournament</i>
<i>Nadal hasn't won.</i>

137
00:07:53.556 --> 00:07:54.599
[Rafa] <i>Pressure.</i>

138
00:07:55.808 --> 00:07:57.226
<i>That's what I felt.</i>

139
00:07:57.852 --> 00:07:59.896
<i>Because. by winning the US Open.</i>

140
00:07:59.979 --> 00:08:02.315
<i>I would have won all four Grand Slams.</i>

141
00:08:02.815 --> 00:08:03.816
<i>For a tennis player.</i>

142
00:08:03.900 --> 00:08:06.402
<i>winning all four Slams is something</i>

143
00:08:06.486 --> 00:08:08.821
<i>that very few people have done.</i>

144
00:08:09.655 --> 00:08:12.450
[commentator 2] <i>Tennis fans</i>
<i>around the world hoping it will be</i>

145
00:08:12.533 --> 00:08:14.535
<i>this man and Roger Federer.</i>

146
00:08:14.619 --> 00:08:18.456
<i>Everybody around the world is…</i>
<i>wants that final so badly.</i>

147
00:08:23.961 --> 00:08:25.087
[music fades]

148
00:08:25.171 --> 00:08:27.173
[commentator 1]
<i>Live from the men's championship.</i>

149
00:08:27.256 --> 00:08:29.926
<i>world number 1. Rafa Nadal.</i>

150
00:08:30.885 --> 00:08:34.013
<i>against number 3 seed. Novak Djokovic.</i>

151
00:08:34.096 --> 00:08:36.098
[foreboding music playing]

152
00:08:38.601 --> 00:08:40.603
[Novak] <i>Rafa and Roger in the finals.</i>

153
00:08:40.686 --> 00:08:43.064
<i>That was the scenario</i>
<i>everybody wants to see.</i>

154
00:08:43.564 --> 00:08:45.858
But I didn't care. Actually…

155
00:08:46.609 --> 00:08:50.279
{\an8}I did care to not allow that to happen.

156
00:08:50.780 --> 00:08:51.822
[cheering]

157
00:08:51.906 --> 00:08:55.576
[commentator 2] <i>Now. of course.</i>
<i>with Novak Djokovic as well. in the mix.</i>

158
00:08:55.660 --> 00:08:57.662
[soft battle music playing]

159
00:08:58.246 --> 00:08:59.205
[Rafa] <i>At that moment.</i>

160
00:08:59.288 --> 00:09:03.834
I saw the danger that not only Roger
was fighting for number 1.

161
00:09:03.918 --> 00:09:06.045
But Novak was also coming in.

162
00:09:07.463 --> 00:09:08.881
[crowd cheering]

163
00:09:08.965 --> 00:09:11.634
[Clarey] <i>Nadal and Novak.</i>
<i>they had a history.</i>

164
00:09:12.134 --> 00:09:15.388
{\an8}They had played for the first time
on tour at the French Open. 2006.

165
00:09:17.974 --> 00:09:20.268
<i>Novak made his first big run at a major.</i>

166
00:09:20.351 --> 00:09:22.061
But he hadn't done much until then.

167
00:09:22.937 --> 00:09:26.440
<i>And he ended up losing</i>
<i>the first two sets to Rafa. 6-4. 6-4.</i>

168
00:09:26.524 --> 00:09:28.192
<i>Then he retired citing a back injury.</i>

169
00:09:28.276 --> 00:09:29.819
[umpire] Game. set. and match. Nadal.

170
00:09:29.902 --> 00:09:33.072
Even though he's the best
and everybody thinks he's unbeatable.

171
00:09:33.155 --> 00:09:35.241
I say he's not unbeatable. he's beatable.

172
00:09:35.324 --> 00:09:36.617
Are you kidding me?

173
00:09:36.701 --> 00:09:38.661
Djokovic. do you need some smelling salts?

174
00:09:38.744 --> 00:09:40.871
<i>It was a heavyweight</i>
<i>versus a middleweight.</i>

175
00:09:40.955 --> 00:09:42.540
<i>You were being pushed back.</i>

176
00:09:42.623 --> 00:09:46.794
It felt like Rafa and Roger
were crafted by the tennis gods.

177
00:09:48.838 --> 00:09:52.550
<i>And so I had to fight</i>
<i>for my place under the sun.</i>

178
00:09:53.134 --> 00:09:54.260
[crowd cheering]

179
00:09:56.137 --> 00:09:59.682
{\an8}Djokovic is totally different
in character from Roger and Rafa.

180
00:10:00.391 --> 00:10:03.853
<i>I mean. he was someone</i>
<i>who was constantly making jokes.</i>

181
00:10:03.936 --> 00:10:07.273
{\an8}He was doing these imitations of players.
including Rafa.

182
00:10:08.065 --> 00:10:09.609
[crowd laughing. applauding]

183
00:10:09.692 --> 00:10:11.319
[Rafa] <i>He wasn't a shy person.</i>

184
00:10:13.571 --> 00:10:16.282
It really didn't… bother me.

185
00:10:16.365 --> 00:10:17.825
<i>No.</i>

186
00:10:18.409 --> 00:10:19.535
<i>Although. it…</i>

187
00:10:20.620 --> 00:10:21.579
[blows air]

188
00:10:21.662 --> 00:10:24.081
I don't remember very well
if it bothered me.

189
00:10:24.165 --> 00:10:26.375
 Not much. Surely. not much.

190
00:10:28.127 --> 00:10:32.757
[commentator] <i>Rafa Nadal. So much</i>
<i>at stake for this 24-year-old Spaniard.</i>

191
00:10:32.840 --> 00:10:34.967
[expectant music playing]

192
00:10:47.438 --> 00:10:48.481
[commentator] <i>Wow!</i>

193
00:10:48.564 --> 00:10:51.442
<i>Djokovic would've won this point</i>
<i>against anyone else.</i>

194
00:10:51.525 --> 00:10:53.736
[Toni] <i>When you looked at Djokovic.</i>

195
00:10:53.819 --> 00:10:57.239
you could tell he was confident
because he was playing really well.

196
00:10:58.157 --> 00:11:00.076
<i>That could be a big problem.</i>

197
00:11:00.159 --> 00:11:01.952
[commentator 2]
<i>Djokovic. with all this effort.</i>

198
00:11:02.036 --> 00:11:06.040
<i>it's even now more incredible</i>
<i>what Nadal's pulling off.</i>

199
00:11:10.419 --> 00:11:12.421
[cheering erupts]

200
00:11:13.172 --> 00:11:15.341
[commentator 3] <i>His career slam is grand.</i>

201
00:11:16.133 --> 00:11:17.718
<i>Rafael Nadal!</i>

202
00:11:18.219 --> 00:11:20.930
<i>The final jewel in his crown.</i>

203
00:11:21.681 --> 00:11:23.683
[dynamic upbeat music playing]

204
00:11:23.766 --> 00:11:26.268
[presenter] <i>Please welcome</i>
<i>US Open Men's Champion.</i>

205
00:11:26.352 --> 00:11:27.395
<i>Rafael Nadal!</i>

206
00:11:29.939 --> 00:11:32.108
[Rafa] <i>After winning the US Open.</i>

207
00:11:32.191 --> 00:11:34.276
<i>it was a bit of a media frenzy.</i>

208
00:11:34.360 --> 00:11:35.569
[shutters clicking]

209
00:11:35.653 --> 00:11:37.405
[fan] Rafa. I love you!

210
00:11:38.322 --> 00:11:40.116
[Rafa] <i>But I've never liked</i>

211
00:11:40.991 --> 00:11:42.827
being the center of attention.

212
00:11:43.786 --> 00:11:46.163
[David Letterman]
<i>Please welcome Rafael Nadal.</i>

213
00:11:46.247 --> 00:11:47.623
[applause]

214
00:11:47.707 --> 00:11:51.419
{\an8}I remember a lot of media telling me.
"He's gonna love to do this." Well…

215
00:11:52.336 --> 00:11:54.588
<i>I would say. in a very polite way.</i>

216
00:11:54.672 --> 00:11:56.507
"No. that's not the right word."

217
00:11:56.590 --> 00:11:58.426
I have no idea what this is.

218
00:11:58.509 --> 00:12:00.469
[audience laughs]

219
00:12:01.220 --> 00:12:03.222
[Letterman]
Looks like you in your underpants.

220
00:12:03.305 --> 00:12:05.599
[Benito] <i>He knew it was part of his job.</i>

221
00:12:05.683 --> 00:12:08.602
but. yeah.
doing something out of his comfort zone.

222
00:12:08.686 --> 00:12:09.937
you know. was not easy.

223
00:12:10.980 --> 00:12:14.442
[Rafa] <i>I remember when I went</i>
<i>to do a music video with Shakira.</i>

224
00:12:15.526 --> 00:12:20.030
I had to ask for a bottle of tequila
to drink a few shots to relax a bit.

225
00:12:20.114 --> 00:12:21.365
[energetic music playing]

226
00:12:21.449 --> 00:12:23.075
- [clamoring]
- [shutters clicking]

227
00:12:23.159 --> 00:12:24.952
[interviewer] <i>You're kind of a sex symbol.</i>

228
00:12:25.035 --> 00:12:26.120
[Rafa] <i>No. I don't know…</i>

229
00:12:26.203 --> 00:12:29.123
I really never stop to think these things.

230
00:12:29.206 --> 00:12:31.417
So. Rafael. uh. you got a girlfriend?

231
00:12:31.500 --> 00:12:32.835
[laughter]

232
00:12:32.918 --> 00:12:33.919
I have.

233
00:12:34.420 --> 00:12:37.006
I can't get over the way
you're flirting with him!

234
00:12:37.089 --> 00:12:38.716
{\an8}[music fades]

235
00:12:39.467 --> 00:12:42.470
{\an8}People don't know
that he is. in essence. a shy person.

236
00:12:42.553 --> 00:12:43.929
[shutters clicking]

237
00:12:46.056 --> 00:12:47.224
Good luck. Nadal!

238
00:12:48.142 --> 00:12:51.103
[María] <i>We grew up in a very small town.</i>

239
00:12:51.187 --> 00:12:53.189
[nostalgic music playing]

240
00:12:54.315 --> 00:12:57.109
Our families knew each other

241
00:12:57.193 --> 00:12:59.278
since before we were born.

242
00:13:00.863 --> 00:13:04.450
<i>I remember. for example.</i>
<i>being at Rafa's first communion.</i>

243
00:13:06.035 --> 00:13:08.496
But. of course.
I would've been six years old.

244
00:13:10.164 --> 00:13:14.627
<i>We got to know each other better</i>
<i>when we were teenagers.</i>

245
00:13:16.337 --> 00:13:19.298
<i>I remember we started dating</i>
<i>during a summer.</i>

246
00:13:19.381 --> 00:13:21.884
It was 2000…
It must've been the summer of…

247
00:13:21.967 --> 00:13:24.637
I'm really bad at these things.
Rafa's gonna kill me.

248
00:13:25.387 --> 00:13:27.264
[man] You're good
with those text messages. huh?

249
00:13:27.348 --> 00:13:28.224
[Rafa] Well…

250
00:13:29.433 --> 00:13:31.769
[María] <i>He was chasing me</i>
<i>during that time.</i>

251
00:13:33.103 --> 00:13:36.524
[Rafa] <i>I started sending her</i>
<i>some messages and…</i>

252
00:13:36.607 --> 00:13:39.735
she would reply.
but without much interest.

253
00:13:39.819 --> 00:13:41.904
[man] Don't be sad. She'll come around.

254
00:13:41.987 --> 00:13:44.240
- I'm a mess right now.
- [laughter]

255
00:13:44.824 --> 00:13:45.866
Mary!

256
00:13:46.492 --> 00:13:48.035
Answer. please!

257
00:13:48.118 --> 00:13:49.745
- [indistinct]
- [cellphone rings]

258
00:13:49.829 --> 00:13:50.955
Wha…!

259
00:13:53.123 --> 00:13:54.583
<i>I was in love with her.</i>

260
00:13:55.417 --> 00:13:58.212
<i>She gave me the inner strength…</i>

261
00:13:59.338 --> 00:14:01.173
<i>to maintain stability</i>

262
00:14:02.049 --> 00:14:03.467
<i>when I really needed it.</i>

263
00:14:03.551 --> 00:14:05.344
[emotional music playing]

264
00:14:05.845 --> 00:14:08.556
Rafa really likes to be at home.

265
00:14:09.682 --> 00:14:12.351
<i>with his family. in Mallorca…</i>

266
00:14:13.811 --> 00:14:18.357
[Rafa] <i>I lived at home</i>
<i>with my parents until I was…</i>

267
00:14:18.440 --> 00:14:20.526
31? 32?

268
00:14:21.110 --> 00:14:23.571
I never felt like leaving. No.

269
00:14:25.531 --> 00:14:29.410
[Maribel] <i>In our family.</i>
<i>we have always been very close.</i>

270
00:14:34.415 --> 00:14:38.252
<i>When we were living in Manacor.</i>
<i>our grandparents lived on the first floor.</i>

271
00:14:38.752 --> 00:14:41.964
<i>Toni on the second floor.</i>
<i>and we were on the third.</i>

272
00:14:42.923 --> 00:14:44.300
<i>So ever since he was a kid.</i>

273
00:14:44.383 --> 00:14:47.970
<i>he's always spent</i>
<i>a lot of time with our family.</i>

274
00:14:51.015 --> 00:14:53.976
<i>And I think that</i>
<i>this has also made him grow up</i>

275
00:14:54.059 --> 00:14:58.188
in a very family-oriented
and also very safe environment.

276
00:14:58.272 --> 00:15:01.108
- [indistinct chatter]
- [laughter]

277
00:15:09.825 --> 00:15:11.619
[Rafa] <i>To me. being at home.</i>

278
00:15:12.494 --> 00:15:13.495
<i>I feel like</i>

279
00:15:13.996 --> 00:15:16.874
<i>I can be more myself.</i>

280
00:15:18.584 --> 00:15:21.170
Jerry! Eat this. There's some left.

281
00:15:21.253 --> 00:15:23.839
- [indistinct chatter]
- [laughing]

282
00:15:25.299 --> 00:15:27.843
[Rafa] <i>I feel like I can be more myself.</i>

283
00:15:28.427 --> 00:15:30.471
Which are the ones with Nutella?

284
00:15:31.555 --> 00:15:33.349
<i>And live like someone…</i>

285
00:15:33.974 --> 00:15:35.309
<i>with a normal life.</i>

286
00:15:37.561 --> 00:15:40.731
[Rafa] Rafelet!? What a miss! Way off!

287
00:15:40.814 --> 00:15:42.524
[woman] Incredible!

288
00:15:43.859 --> 00:15:46.028
[Rafa] Okay. focus. One more try.

289
00:15:47.154 --> 00:15:49.490
Good! That was so good!

290
00:15:53.911 --> 00:15:56.538
[Rafa] This is good. Really good.

291
00:15:57.122 --> 00:16:00.209
- [María] I only wanted a small piece.
- No. go ahead. eat.

292
00:16:00.793 --> 00:16:02.628
You're at your best right now.

293
00:16:04.088 --> 00:16:05.589
[Rafa laughs warmly]

294
00:16:06.173 --> 00:16:07.549
You don't notice. but…

295
00:16:09.885 --> 00:16:12.554
you're at a point
where you look spectacular.

296
00:16:15.182 --> 00:16:16.517
Did you treat me?

297
00:16:20.396 --> 00:16:22.439
[poignant music playing]

298
00:16:26.193 --> 00:16:29.363
[commentator 1] <i>At the end of the day.</i>
<i>Rafa got in three wins in Madrid.</i>

299
00:16:29.446 --> 00:16:31.240
<i>He was able to make some strides.</i>

300
00:16:31.323 --> 00:16:34.994
<i>Proved to himself that he could play</i>
<i>match after match. healthwise.</i>

301
00:16:35.077 --> 00:16:37.746
<i>What's your biggest takeaway</i>
<i>from this tournament for Nadal?</i>

302
00:16:37.830 --> 00:16:40.082
[commentator 2] <i>My biggest takeaway</i>
<i>is there's optimism.</i>

303
00:16:43.335 --> 00:16:44.545
[Moyá] Brutal. man.

304
00:16:45.421 --> 00:16:47.047
- Mentally. he's doing well.
- What?

305
00:16:47.131 --> 00:16:48.424
His head's in a good place today.

306
00:16:48.507 --> 00:16:51.552
[commentator 2] <i>Now it's…</i>
<i>He has a week. effectively.</i>

307
00:16:51.635 --> 00:16:53.595
<i>before he would start in Rome.</i>

308
00:16:53.679 --> 00:16:56.682
<i>Ultimately. he's playing</i>
<i>the long game for Roland-Garros.</i>

309
00:16:56.765 --> 00:16:59.268
[commentator 1]
<i>If he feels the way he's felt this week.</i>

310
00:16:59.351 --> 00:17:01.395
<i>he will be playing Roland-Garros.</i>

311
00:17:02.896 --> 00:17:05.816
[María] <i>He's having his best moment</i>
<i>since last year.</i>

312
00:17:07.860 --> 00:17:10.237
<i>And in the end. what matters is that…</i>

313
00:17:12.406 --> 00:17:14.408
<i>he sees himself playing well.</i>

314
00:17:15.826 --> 00:17:19.371
<i>And to have his son see him lift a trophy.</i>

315
00:17:20.414 --> 00:17:22.249
<i>that's what he wants most in life.</i>

316
00:17:22.332 --> 00:17:25.210
<i>And. of course.</i>
<i>for his son to see him win.</i>

317
00:17:25.711 --> 00:17:27.713
[Rafa exclaims playfully]

318
00:17:27.796 --> 00:17:29.423
[cheering rises]

319
00:17:29.506 --> 00:17:30.799
[announcer] <i>Ladies and gentlemen.</i>

320
00:17:30.883 --> 00:17:34.720
the winner of the 2010
US Open Men's Championship.

321
00:17:34.803 --> 00:17:36.805
Rafael Nadal!

322
00:17:38.348 --> 00:17:41.518
[Rafa] <i>At that time.</i>
<i>I was the best player in the world.</i>

323
00:17:43.145 --> 00:17:44.563
<i>But that's never enough.</i>

324
00:17:46.065 --> 00:17:50.152
<i>To be the best player in the world.</i>
<i>you have to prove it in every tournament.</i>

325
00:17:50.235 --> 00:17:51.570
[music fades]

326
00:17:52.237 --> 00:17:55.491
[commentator 1] <i>Let's transition now</i>
<i>to the men's singles final.</i>

327
00:17:56.158 --> 00:17:59.620
[commentator 2] <i>Rafael Nadal.</i>
<i>the number 1 ranked player in the world.</i>

328
00:17:59.703 --> 00:18:02.122
<i>taking on Novak Djokovic.</i>

329
00:18:02.623 --> 00:18:06.710
[commentator 3] <i>The hottest player.</i>
<i>Hasn't fared well in finals against Rafa.</i>

330
00:18:06.794 --> 00:18:08.796
<i>so that's a big asterisk.</i>

331
00:18:09.755 --> 00:18:12.674
[Ángel] <i>The feeling with Djokovic was.</i>
<i>he's very good.</i>

332
00:18:12.758 --> 00:18:16.095
but he's still not able to beat
the best when it really matters.

333
00:18:16.178 --> 00:18:17.554
[intriguing music playing]

334
00:18:18.639 --> 00:18:20.641
But in 2011. the threat becomes real.

335
00:18:27.147 --> 00:18:28.065
[indistinct]

336
00:18:29.233 --> 00:18:31.360
Everybody wants to take down the number 1.

337
00:18:33.112 --> 00:18:36.657
<i>So. being the hunter oftentimes is better.</i>

338
00:18:37.241 --> 00:18:38.826
<i>Because you feel like</i>

339
00:18:39.326 --> 00:18:42.955
you want to fight for your success.
rather than defend it.

340
00:18:44.331 --> 00:18:47.417
[commentator 3]
<i>Djokovic takes a commanding lead!</i>

341
00:18:47.501 --> 00:18:49.586
So. it's a psychological battle.

342
00:18:50.170 --> 00:18:52.548
[commentator 3]
<i>I see frustration from Nadal now.</i>

343
00:18:52.631 --> 00:18:54.341
<i>Don't see that very often.</i>

344
00:18:54.424 --> 00:18:55.467
[music builds]

345
00:18:55.551 --> 00:18:59.429
There comes a time
when players who are very good…

346
00:19:01.807 --> 00:19:02.766
[commentator 3] Oh!

347
00:19:02.850 --> 00:19:06.270
…can make drastic changes
in a short amount of time.

348
00:19:07.729 --> 00:19:10.983
[commentator 3]
<i>Novak Djokovic is your champion here!</i>

349
00:19:13.235 --> 00:19:17.322
<i>We'll see how far Djokovic</i>
<i>can take this momentum.</i>

350
00:19:18.115 --> 00:19:20.993
{\an8}The next match together.
they played again in a final.

351
00:19:21.076 --> 00:19:22.244
Now in Miami.

352
00:19:25.205 --> 00:19:27.833
<i>Now. he is the one with the pressure.</i>

353
00:19:28.417 --> 00:19:30.502
[intriguing music continues]

354
00:19:31.670 --> 00:19:35.549
[Roig] <i>With Djokovic.</i>
<i>the matches were very tough.</i>

355
00:19:36.258 --> 00:19:38.260
[commentator] <i>You got to be kidding me!</i>

356
00:19:38.343 --> 00:19:40.637
{\an8}Rafa always said.
"If I play against Federer.

357
00:19:40.721 --> 00:19:43.182
{\an8}I know that if I play six.
seven good shots.

358
00:19:43.265 --> 00:19:45.017
{\an8}I'm probably going to win the point."

359
00:19:46.685 --> 00:19:48.979
[commentator]
<i>How does he get a racket on that?</i>

360
00:19:49.479 --> 00:19:52.441
"Against Djokovic.
I could hit 15 and still lose."

361
00:19:55.360 --> 00:19:57.237
- [commentator 2] <i>He's done it!</i>
- [crowd cheering]

362
00:20:00.824 --> 00:20:02.951
[Rafa] <i>When I lose the final in Miami.</i>

363
00:20:03.660 --> 00:20:06.705
I realized that my mind
isn't reacting like it used to.

364
00:20:07.289 --> 00:20:08.874
[announcer] Novak Djokovic.

365
00:20:09.374 --> 00:20:11.793
[commentator]
<i>Djokovic hasn't lost a match all year.</i>

366
00:20:12.794 --> 00:20:17.925
<i>But. of course. let's not forget</i>
<i>that he's never beaten Nadal on clay.</i>

367
00:20:19.760 --> 00:20:23.472
[Novak] <i>You could sense</i>
<i>that there's some doubt in him.</i>

368
00:20:23.555 --> 00:20:25.974
and I wanted him to feel that.

369
00:20:26.058 --> 00:20:27.517
[tense music playing]

370
00:20:36.735 --> 00:20:38.195
[music builds]

371
00:20:38.779 --> 00:20:41.448
[commentator] <i>Victory for Djokovic</i>

372
00:20:41.531 --> 00:20:43.367
<i>on the Spaniard's beloved clay.</i>

373
00:20:46.286 --> 00:20:49.748
There's a moment
when you start to lose your confidence.

374
00:20:50.916 --> 00:20:53.502
<i>And it's the fish that bites its own tail.</i>

375
00:20:54.211 --> 00:20:56.838
I start failing. I lose confidence.

376
00:20:56.922 --> 00:20:58.882
I lose confidence. I fail even more.

377
00:20:58.966 --> 00:21:02.719
[commentator] <i>Oh!</i>
<i>Djokovic is the champion in Rome!</i>

378
00:21:03.220 --> 00:21:05.472
That's where I felt.
"Okay. I got in his head.

379
00:21:05.555 --> 00:21:07.099
now I just need to keep going."

380
00:21:07.683 --> 00:21:10.644
I had in my head that he had surpassed me.

381
00:21:11.436 --> 00:21:15.357
[commentator] <i>And it's been Nadal.</i>
<i>who at critical junctures. has missed.</i>

382
00:21:16.441 --> 00:21:18.986
<i>Which we're so not used</i>
<i>to seeing that from Rafa.</i>

383
00:21:23.073 --> 00:21:24.157
- Out!
- <i>That's wide.</i>

384
00:21:24.241 --> 00:21:26.785
[commentator] <i>Novak Djokovic</i>
<i>is your champion here</i>

385
00:21:26.868 --> 00:21:30.706
<i>and. you'd have to say.</i>
<i>he's the best player in the world.</i>

386
00:21:31.290 --> 00:21:34.042
[commentator 2]
<i>Now. that is five straight victories</i>

387
00:21:34.126 --> 00:21:36.295
<i>over Rafa Nadal.</i>

388
00:21:36.795 --> 00:21:40.090
[Wertheim] <i>I remember Rafa</i>
<i>walks into that press conference.</i>

389
00:21:41.341 --> 00:21:44.386
<i>A guy who was sort of dazed.</i>

390
00:21:46.305 --> 00:21:48.307
<i>You had a feeling Novak had. like…</i>

391
00:21:49.433 --> 00:21:50.851
taken his soul.

392
00:21:51.601 --> 00:21:55.439
I lose because I'm playing against
the best player of the moment.

393
00:21:55.522 --> 00:21:58.650
the best player of the world. tomorrow.

394
00:21:58.734 --> 00:21:59.776
And…

395
00:22:00.485 --> 00:22:01.903
[music fades]

396
00:22:01.987 --> 00:22:03.405
…and I am the second.

397
00:22:03.905 --> 00:22:07.409
The great Rafa Nadal
now seemed kind of broken.

398
00:22:08.577 --> 00:22:12.039
[announcer] 2011 US Open
Men's Singles Champion.

399
00:22:12.122 --> 00:22:13.957
Novak Djokovic!

400
00:22:15.542 --> 00:22:16.877
[Toni] <i>It was a disaster.</i>

401
00:22:19.046 --> 00:22:21.757
<i>He couldn't fight anymore.</i>
<i>He didn't know how.</i>

402
00:22:25.427 --> 00:22:27.012
<i>It's a stressful time</i>

403
00:22:27.512 --> 00:22:29.181
<i>that you have to overcome.</i>

404
00:22:29.264 --> 00:22:31.516
- [racket strikes]
- [Rafa grunts]

405
00:22:31.600 --> 00:22:34.853
And if you don't overcome it.
then you stop being good.

406
00:22:35.437 --> 00:22:37.439
[poignant music playing]

407
00:22:39.649 --> 00:22:43.987
{\an8}Toni has helped him a lot
to become as strong as he has been.

408
00:22:44.780 --> 00:22:49.368
<i>But as a mother.</i>
<i>I was worried about all that pressure.</i>

409
00:22:49.868 --> 00:22:54.122
Because he started
to have to fight battles in his head

410
00:22:54.206 --> 00:22:56.708
 at a very young age.

411
00:23:01.505 --> 00:23:04.007
"It always seems
like I have to be better."

412
00:23:05.217 --> 00:23:07.552
"It always seems like it's not enough."

413
00:23:08.845 --> 00:23:11.223
"It always seems
like you have to go higher."

414
00:23:12.516 --> 00:23:14.643
[reporter in Spanish]
<i>Rafael Nadal has been confirmed</i>

415
00:23:14.726 --> 00:23:17.145
<i>as the best under-14 player in Spain.</i>

416
00:23:17.771 --> 00:23:21.358
[Ana María in English] <i>That even if</i>
<i>you get higher. you won't be the best.</i>

417
00:23:21.441 --> 00:23:23.443
<i>You have to go even higher.</i>

418
00:23:23.527 --> 00:23:27.197
- [interviewer] <i>What do you plan to do now?</i>
- [young Rafa] <i>Continue training. I guess.</i>

419
00:23:27.280 --> 00:23:30.075
I don't know.
I think this tournament is important.

420
00:23:30.158 --> 00:23:32.619
but winning this tournament doesn't mean

421
00:23:32.702 --> 00:23:35.747
that you are already a very good player.

422
00:23:37.082 --> 00:23:39.793
[Ana María]
<i>All this creates insecurities in you.</i>

423
00:23:41.378 --> 00:23:45.549
[commentator] <i>And here we go again.</i>
<i>Sock. The hair is coming next.</i>

424
00:23:47.634 --> 00:23:49.761
[María] <i>As time has gone by.</i>

425
00:23:49.845 --> 00:23:52.013
he has been adding routines.

426
00:23:52.097 --> 00:23:54.850
- Come on. Rafael!
- Come on!

427
00:23:56.059 --> 00:23:57.310
[umpire] Time.

428
00:23:59.604 --> 00:24:00.689
This. this.

429
00:24:00.772 --> 00:24:03.692
the bottles. this.
the lines. this. waiting…

430
00:24:03.775 --> 00:24:07.154
So I told him. "Well. stop doing it.
We're making a fool of ourselves."

431
00:24:10.073 --> 00:24:15.328
There were times when I tried
to get rid of some routines.

432
00:24:18.248 --> 00:24:20.375
<i>Because. when I saw myself on TV.</i>

433
00:24:20.459 --> 00:24:23.086
<i>I didn't like to see myself</i>
<i>doing those things.</i>

434
00:24:23.587 --> 00:24:25.213
But. uh…

435
00:24:26.798 --> 00:24:28.008
But I couldn't.

436
00:24:29.009 --> 00:24:30.093
I needed them.

437
00:24:32.095 --> 00:24:34.055
<i>They made me feel safe.</i>

438
00:24:37.350 --> 00:24:39.227
Everyone feels pressure.

439
00:24:40.270 --> 00:24:42.564
<i>But. of course. that's why you're good.</i>

440
00:24:44.065 --> 00:24:46.151
<i>Because you can handle that pressure.</i>

441
00:24:52.032 --> 00:24:52.991
[music stops]

442
00:24:57.287 --> 00:25:00.582
[commentator] <i>Another week of training.</i>
<i>Getting back into the rhythm. into shape.</i>

443
00:25:00.665 --> 00:25:02.209
<i>Three. four matches in Rome.</i>

444
00:25:02.292 --> 00:25:04.753
[commentator 2] <i>I don't think</i>
<i>he should put pressure on himself.</i>

445
00:25:04.836 --> 00:25:07.797
<i>He has to go out there and play.</i>
<i>See how things go.</i>

446
00:25:11.384 --> 00:25:13.386
[Gustavo]
There was an unevenness on this side.

447
00:25:13.470 --> 00:25:15.222
 but not on that side.

448
00:25:16.181 --> 00:25:17.766
That one was much less.

449
00:25:19.267 --> 00:25:21.269
[diligent music playing]

450
00:25:24.439 --> 00:25:26.816
- [Moyá] You play backhand to him. okay?
- Okay.

451
00:25:26.900 --> 00:25:28.610
[Moyá] Hit hard. Let's see that forehand.

452
00:25:34.032 --> 00:25:36.493
To me. it's all about
him controlling his mind.

453
00:25:36.993 --> 00:25:40.413
If he's nervous.
he volleys badly. hits badly.

454
00:25:40.497 --> 00:25:42.207
moves all over the place.

455
00:25:42.791 --> 00:25:45.669
He's slow. reacts late.
gets uncoordinated. all that.

456
00:25:48.338 --> 00:25:49.422
And when he's calm…

457
00:25:51.299 --> 00:25:52.926
everything's better. man.

458
00:25:58.765 --> 00:26:01.017
- [Gustavo] Do a reset now. yeah?
- Come on.

459
00:26:01.101 --> 00:26:03.353
[Rafa] I've been resetting
the whole training session

460
00:26:03.436 --> 00:26:05.188
 because I keep acting like a moron.

461
00:26:07.107 --> 00:26:09.150
[reporter] <i>What is it</i>
<i>that you need the most?</i>

462
00:26:09.234 --> 00:26:11.695
What we need the most is…

463
00:26:12.195 --> 00:26:13.697
to beat Djokovic.

464
00:26:17.826 --> 00:26:20.161
[Rafa] <i>Novak was winning the mental battle</i>

465
00:26:20.662 --> 00:26:22.539
and I needed to change that.

466
00:26:24.541 --> 00:26:27.168
[Toni] <i>To me.</i>
<i>it's not just a mental issue.</i>

467
00:26:27.252 --> 00:26:28.920
<i>it's a preparation issue.</i>

468
00:26:30.046 --> 00:26:33.008
I can give you confidence.
once you are prepared.

469
00:26:33.592 --> 00:26:35.885
[smooth resolute music playing]

470
00:26:35.969 --> 00:26:37.470
[Toni] <i>The change was the forehand.</i>

471
00:26:37.554 --> 00:26:39.264
A more aggressive forehand.

472
00:26:40.849 --> 00:26:43.018
<i>I remember showing him clips.</i>

473
00:26:43.101 --> 00:26:47.772
<i>I told him. "Federer and Djokovic.</i>
<i>when they hit a winner. they jump."</i>

474
00:26:48.940 --> 00:26:51.693
<i>With that. they get an extra</i>
<i>in terms of speed</i>

475
00:26:51.776 --> 00:26:55.322
<i>and. more importantly.</i>
<i>an extra to their will to win.</i>

476
00:26:56.990 --> 00:26:59.492
<i>I made him hit winners from this side.</i>

477
00:26:59.576 --> 00:27:02.537
<i>from that side. from here. from there…</i>

478
00:27:03.246 --> 00:27:04.289
Come on.

479
00:27:07.208 --> 00:27:09.711
[Rafa] <i>Toni helped me</i>
<i>change the situation.</i>

480
00:27:09.794 --> 00:27:12.714
<i>I was starting to feel mentally prepared.</i>

481
00:27:12.797 --> 00:27:14.299
[cheering rises]

482
00:27:14.382 --> 00:27:16.384
[hopeful ethereal music playing]

483
00:27:20.513 --> 00:27:21.890
[cheering continues]

484
00:27:24.934 --> 00:27:26.686
[commentator 1]
<i>What a match it's going to be.</i>

485
00:27:27.187 --> 00:27:31.149
<i>They are both at the top of their game.</i>
<i>The two best players in the world.</i>

486
00:27:31.650 --> 00:27:36.071
<i>The difference for Rafael Nadal</i>
<i>this time is that he is number 2.</i>

487
00:27:36.988 --> 00:27:38.031
<i>He is the hunter.</i>

488
00:27:39.074 --> 00:27:39.991
<i>rather than the hunted.</i>

489
00:27:41.993 --> 00:27:43.119
[music fades]

490
00:27:49.000 --> 00:27:52.420
[commentator 2] <i>There's the forehand.</i>
<i>This is the one that does the damage.</i>

491
00:27:52.504 --> 00:27:55.507
I don't know what happened.
but he was so aggressive.

492
00:27:56.299 --> 00:27:58.301
[rousing battle music playing]

493
00:28:00.387 --> 00:28:03.973
[Rafa] <i>My forehands were more damaging</i>
<i>than a few months before.</i>

494
00:28:06.351 --> 00:28:09.270
[commentator 2] <i>An incredible forehand.</i>
<i>that's the favorite shot.</i>

495
00:28:09.354 --> 00:28:12.107
[commentator 1]
<i>Rafael Nadal takes the first set</i>

496
00:28:12.190 --> 00:28:14.401
<i>after one hour and twenty minutes.</i>

497
00:28:15.318 --> 00:28:17.946
[Rafa] <i>But. even though I may feel better.</i>

498
00:28:18.029 --> 00:28:22.075
I also think about what happened
a few months before.

499
00:28:24.160 --> 00:28:25.078
{\an8}[crowd exclaims]

500
00:28:25.662 --> 00:28:28.081
[commentator 1]
<i>Djokovic levels up the match.</i>

501
00:28:31.292 --> 00:28:32.794
[music intensifies]

502
00:28:39.008 --> 00:28:41.094
[commentator 2]
<i>Djokovic looks so confident.</i>

503
00:28:41.177 --> 00:28:44.556
[commentator 1] <i>In contrast.</i>
<i>the look on Rafa's face told a lot.</i>

504
00:28:45.557 --> 00:28:47.767
[commentator 3]
<i>You can sense that Nadal's thinking.</i>

505
00:28:47.851 --> 00:28:49.185
<i>"This is déjà vu."</i>

506
00:28:49.686 --> 00:28:53.648
[commentator 2] <i>It is going to take</i>
<i>a Herculean effort from the Spaniard</i>

507
00:28:53.732 --> 00:28:56.192
<i>to take it out to five sets.</i>

508
00:28:57.110 --> 00:28:58.778
[Rafa] <i>Throughout the whole year.</i>

509
00:28:58.862 --> 00:29:01.406
when the important moments
against Novak came.

510
00:29:02.198 --> 00:29:06.035
<i>I'd feel that. mentally.</i>
<i>I didn't fully believe</i>

511
00:29:06.119 --> 00:29:07.203
that I could win.

512
00:29:09.914 --> 00:29:12.834
<i>But here. what I had been feeling…</i>

513
00:29:14.627 --> 00:29:15.712
[line] Out!

514
00:29:16.755 --> 00:29:17.922
…was changing.

515
00:29:18.923 --> 00:29:21.259
[commentator 1] <i>It is two sets apiece.</i>

516
00:29:24.721 --> 00:29:28.808
<i>Nadal collapses to his knees</i>
<i>and then bounces straight back up.</i>

517
00:29:28.892 --> 00:29:32.520
<i>because he knows</i>
<i>the job is still there to be done.</i>

518
00:29:32.604 --> 00:29:36.441
[commentator 3] <i>This is the first time</i>
<i>Nadal truly believes that he can win.</i>

519
00:29:36.524 --> 00:29:38.401
<i>He's been hoping. he's been wanting.</i>

520
00:29:38.485 --> 00:29:41.488
<i>but this is the first time</i>
<i>he truly believes it.</i>

521
00:29:42.655 --> 00:29:46.993
[commentator 1] <i>Officially.</i>
<i>the longest Grand Slam final in history.</i>

522
00:29:51.456 --> 00:29:54.918
[commentator 2] <i>Djokovic stretching</i>
<i>to try and keep limber and loose.</i>

523
00:29:55.001 --> 00:29:56.503
The fifth set was brutal.

524
00:29:58.171 --> 00:30:00.965
I'd say it was physically… devastating.

525
00:30:04.761 --> 00:30:06.137
[commentator 2] <i>Oh. boy!</i>

526
00:30:06.221 --> 00:30:07.847
<i>Djokovic is down.</i>

527
00:30:08.431 --> 00:30:10.266
[commentator 1]
<i>Thirty-one points in the rally.</i>

528
00:30:10.350 --> 00:30:14.020
<i>The crowd just standing and applauding.</i>
<i>They're standing up here.</i>

529
00:30:14.562 --> 00:30:16.397
[Novak] <i>I was really worn out.</i>

530
00:30:16.940 --> 00:30:22.153
<i>Doubt was creeping in more and more</i>
<i>whether I can pull this through.</i>

531
00:30:23.863 --> 00:30:25.782
[Rafa] <i>I was suffering.</i>

532
00:30:26.783 --> 00:30:28.743
But I was also enjoying

533
00:30:28.827 --> 00:30:31.996
seeing myself once again competing

534
00:30:32.789 --> 00:30:34.040
at the highest level.

535
00:30:34.833 --> 00:30:37.418
[umpire] Nadal leads 4-2.

536
00:30:38.336 --> 00:30:39.712
[Novak] <i>He was a break up.</i>

537
00:30:41.464 --> 00:30:43.508
And I still remember that point.

538
00:30:47.345 --> 00:30:49.848
<i>He plays drop shot.</i>
<i>I play counter drop shot.</i>

539
00:30:51.349 --> 00:30:52.600
A pretty bad one.

540
00:30:52.684 --> 00:30:54.602
[pulsing music playing]

541
00:30:54.686 --> 00:30:57.355
A passing shot. Very. very easy.

542
00:31:00.775 --> 00:31:04.445
<i>By winning this point.</i>
<i>the match was basically won.</i>

543
00:31:09.868 --> 00:31:10.910
[line] Out!

544
00:31:10.994 --> 00:31:13.830
[commentator] <i>Nadal challenges.</i>
<i>The call was a little late.</i>

545
00:31:16.416 --> 00:31:17.625
[commentator 2] <i>Oh. boy!</i>

546
00:31:17.709 --> 00:31:18.918
<i>Can you believe it!</i>

547
00:31:19.002 --> 00:31:21.796
[match replaying on player]

548
00:31:22.297 --> 00:31:23.339
[sound cuts off]

549
00:31:25.633 --> 00:31:26.801
It hurts to watch.

550
00:31:29.762 --> 00:31:31.431
[melancholic music playing]

551
00:31:39.772 --> 00:31:43.192
[commentator] <i>As brave a performance</i>
<i>as Rafael Nadal has produced.</i>

552
00:31:43.276 --> 00:31:45.653
<i>he still walks away empty-handed.</i>

553
00:31:48.740 --> 00:31:50.700
[Rafa] <i>There are times</i>
<i>when you lose a match</i>

554
00:31:50.783 --> 00:31:53.161
<i>and see it in a negative</i>
<i>or a positive way.</i>

555
00:31:54.078 --> 00:31:55.413
[cheering]

556
00:32:01.252 --> 00:32:03.630
[Rafa] <i>And that day I lost the match.</i>

557
00:32:05.048 --> 00:32:10.094
<i>but I wasn't frustrated. or devastated.</i>
<i>or anything like that.</i>

558
00:32:11.888 --> 00:32:12.889
I was satisfied.

559
00:32:15.391 --> 00:32:17.226
<i>I had overcome my mental barrier.</i>

560
00:32:17.727 --> 00:32:19.187
[shutters clicking]

561
00:32:19.270 --> 00:32:20.688
[Rafa] <i>I felt that…</i>

562
00:32:21.773 --> 00:32:23.107
<i>I was back.</i>

563
00:32:23.733 --> 00:32:24.734
[music fades]

564
00:32:24.817 --> 00:32:25.818
[sirens blaring]

565
00:32:31.366 --> 00:32:33.284
[commentator]
<i>Rafa Nadal will be debuting in Rome.</i>

566
00:32:33.368 --> 00:32:36.245
<i>The Masters 1000</i>
<i>is starting today in the Italian capital.</i>

567
00:32:36.329 --> 00:32:38.790
<i>The last tournament</i>
<i>before Roland-Garros begins.</i>

568
00:32:38.873 --> 00:32:40.291
[fans shouting and cheering]

569
00:32:41.376 --> 00:32:44.087
[commentator 2] <i>It's time to push</i>
<i>and see where he is at</i>

570
00:32:44.170 --> 00:32:46.130
<i>and how he can get to Paris.</i>

571
00:32:46.214 --> 00:32:48.549
<i>The key here is to avoid injuries.</i>

572
00:32:49.133 --> 00:32:51.552
<i>And. in Paris. to give it all.</i>

573
00:32:58.393 --> 00:32:59.435
[Moyá] Oh!

574
00:33:01.604 --> 00:33:03.314
He's a completely different player now.

575
00:33:04.565 --> 00:33:05.858
[Moyá] The beast. huh?

576
00:33:06.567 --> 00:33:08.569
[hopeful music playing]

577
00:33:13.199 --> 00:33:17.662
[commentator 1] <i>Almost three hours</i>
<i>on the clock. Nadal looking to seal it.</i>

578
00:33:19.080 --> 00:33:21.082
[applause]

579
00:33:23.334 --> 00:33:25.378
[Moyá] Win using your head. Rafael.

580
00:33:26.295 --> 00:33:27.672
Come on. Rafael! Let's go!

581
00:33:38.182 --> 00:33:40.059
- Ah!
- Come on!

582
00:33:41.144 --> 00:33:43.396
Come on! Come on!

583
00:33:44.355 --> 00:33:47.775
[umpire] 4-6. 6-3. 6-4.

584
00:33:51.529 --> 00:33:55.366
[reporter]<i>Rafa Nadal wins on his return</i>
<i>to the courts of the Italian Open.</i>

585
00:33:55.450 --> 00:33:58.411
<i>This afternoon</i>
<i>we have seen him stronger. more positive.</i>

586
00:33:58.494 --> 00:34:01.372
<i>and fully aware of what he is capable of.</i>

587
00:34:05.543 --> 00:34:07.545
[rising cheers]

588
00:34:11.257 --> 00:34:14.761
{\an8}[announcer] The 2012 champion.
Novak Djokovic!

589
00:34:17.805 --> 00:34:22.185
[Rafa] <i>In 2012.</i>
<i>I'm coming from losing all those finals.</i>

590
00:34:22.268 --> 00:34:24.729
[fans calling] Rafa! Rafa!

591
00:34:24.812 --> 00:34:29.358
[Rafa] <i>But I'm mentally prepared</i>
<i>to try to be able to win.</i>

592
00:34:29.442 --> 00:34:31.444
[tantalizing music playing]

593
00:34:34.822 --> 00:34:37.325
- [man] Come on!
- [umpire] Game. Nadal.

594
00:34:37.992 --> 00:34:39.285
[Maymó] <i>Rafa. in 2012.</i>

595
00:34:39.368 --> 00:34:41.746
is on an upward trend.

596
00:34:43.247 --> 00:34:44.582
[commentator] <i>It's a Rafa special!</i>

597
00:34:45.166 --> 00:34:47.293
[umpire] Game. Nadal!

598
00:34:47.376 --> 00:34:48.961
[crowd cheering]

599
00:34:49.045 --> 00:34:52.131
I had just won at Monte-Carlo.
Barcelona. Rome…

600
00:34:54.008 --> 00:34:56.886
<i>And that's when I started</i>
<i>to feel pain in my knee.</i>

601
00:35:01.557 --> 00:35:04.143
But. at that moment. I wanted to play.

602
00:35:04.227 --> 00:35:06.813
I was feeling good. I wanted to play.
I wanted to win.

603
00:35:10.108 --> 00:35:12.401
<i>With my knee in really bad shape…</i>

604
00:35:12.944 --> 00:35:14.570
[cheering erupts]

605
00:35:14.654 --> 00:35:16.114
<i>…I won Roland-Garros.</i>

606
00:35:16.614 --> 00:35:18.616
[emotional music playing]

607
00:35:19.492 --> 00:35:21.911
[Rafa] <i>So I thought.</i>
<i>I'm gonna be number 1 again.</i>

608
00:35:21.994 --> 00:35:23.955
[announcer] Rafael Nadal!

609
00:35:28.376 --> 00:35:30.503
[Rafa] <i>My knee. in my opinion.</i>

610
00:35:30.586 --> 00:35:32.588
<i>was limiting me quite a bit.</i>

611
00:35:33.506 --> 00:35:35.133
<i>But. I've always felt that.</i>

612
00:35:35.216 --> 00:35:37.051
if my mind is willing.

613
00:35:38.636 --> 00:35:39.679
my body can do it.

614
00:35:46.018 --> 00:35:47.186
[crowd] Whoa!

615
00:35:48.896 --> 00:35:50.356
[dispiriting music playing]

616
00:36:08.416 --> 00:36:10.209
[Rafa] <i>My knee was shattered.</i>

617
00:36:12.879 --> 00:36:16.132
<i>The tendon. basically. had a hole in it.</i>

618
00:36:18.009 --> 00:36:19.051
[music stops]

619
00:36:21.762 --> 00:36:24.807
[reporter 1] <i>Rafa Nadal has withdrawn</i>
<i>from the Olympic Games and the US Open.</i>

620
00:36:24.891 --> 00:36:26.767
<i>where he was a finalist last year.</i>

621
00:36:26.851 --> 00:36:28.519
[shutters clicking]

622
00:36:28.603 --> 00:36:30.605
{\an8}PATELLAR
TENDINOPATHY

623
00:36:31.814 --> 00:36:34.358
[Ruiz-Cotorro]
<i>Those injuries that have been appearing…</i>

624
00:36:34.859 --> 00:36:36.777
{\an8}are not a coincidence.

625
00:36:37.904 --> 00:36:41.032
They are a consequence of a large.
underlying problem.

626
00:36:43.034 --> 00:36:46.829
[Rafa] <i>The fact that I had to play</i>
<i>with an insole throughout my career.</i>

627
00:36:47.955 --> 00:36:50.333
<i>threw the rest of my body outta whack.</i>

628
00:36:51.042 --> 00:36:53.044
[soft adverse music playing]

629
00:36:54.629 --> 00:36:56.714
[Ruiz-Cotorro] <i>From the knee to the foot.</i>

630
00:36:57.590 --> 00:36:58.716
<i>it's a chain.</i>

631
00:37:01.469 --> 00:37:04.222
So we make some changes to the foot.

632
00:37:04.305 --> 00:37:08.184
and those changes
have an impact on the entire chain.

633
00:37:13.439 --> 00:37:17.443
[Maymó] <i>This was an injury that</i>
<i>was not like when you have a fracture.</i>

634
00:37:17.526 --> 00:37:21.197
where you sort of know the time frame
for returning to competition.

635
00:37:24.533 --> 00:37:25.993
[Maymó] Does it hurt?

636
00:37:27.161 --> 00:37:28.412
Okay. Easy then.

637
00:37:28.496 --> 00:37:30.581
[reporter 2] <i>Rafael Nadal</i>
<i>will not be participating</i>

638
00:37:30.665 --> 00:37:31.624
<i>in the Australian Open.</i>

639
00:37:31.707 --> 00:37:35.253
[reporter 1] <i>Novak Djokovic</i>
<i>has won his fourth title in Melbourne.</i>

640
00:37:35.336 --> 00:37:37.255
<i>his third in a row.</i>

641
00:37:37.755 --> 00:37:41.842
<i>Djokovic has made it clear</i>
<i>once again who is number 1.</i>

642
00:37:46.555 --> 00:37:48.766
[Ángel]
<i>After so many months without playing.</i>

643
00:37:48.849 --> 00:37:51.852
there were many people saying.
"Rafa Nadal is finished."

644
00:37:51.936 --> 00:37:53.980
"He's pushed his body to the limit."

645
00:37:54.063 --> 00:37:56.315
<i>"Rafa Nadal will never be the same again."</i>

646
00:37:56.899 --> 00:38:00.069
Rafa Nadal. you've been
out of competition for 102 days.

647
00:38:00.152 --> 00:38:02.321
During all this time. over three months.

648
00:38:02.405 --> 00:38:05.116
have you ever thought that it was the end?

649
00:38:10.871 --> 00:38:13.124
[commentator]
<i>Rafa Nadal's left knee recovery</i>

650
00:38:13.207 --> 00:38:15.167
<i>is not going as quickly as expected.</i>

651
00:38:15.251 --> 00:38:19.297
<i>That's why Nadal might be thinking</i>
<i>of not playing the full Indian Wells.</i>

652
00:38:19.380 --> 00:38:21.799
<i>where he reached the semifinals last year.</i>

653
00:38:21.882 --> 00:38:25.303
[Rafa] <i>The knee hurts either way.</i>
<i>if I'm playing and if I'm not.</i>

654
00:38:26.095 --> 00:38:28.431
So I'd rather keep on playing.

655
00:38:29.765 --> 00:38:31.100
<i>I went to New York…</i>

656
00:38:31.976 --> 00:38:34.895
<i>to see a specialist.</i>

657
00:38:35.730 --> 00:38:37.606
[suspenseful music playing]

658
00:38:38.441 --> 00:38:39.483
<i>I asked the doctor.</i>

659
00:38:39.567 --> 00:38:42.445
<i>"Do you think I can play at Indian Wells.</i>
<i>on hard court? "</i>

660
00:38:43.612 --> 00:38:44.530
<i> He said. "No."</i>

661
00:38:45.906 --> 00:38:49.118
"I don't think you should play.
I don't think you <i>can </i>play."

662
00:38:50.453 --> 00:38:52.830
The doctor told us that it was really bad.

663
00:38:52.913 --> 00:38:55.666
<i>that there was a risk</i>
<i>of irreparable damage.</i>

664
00:38:59.462 --> 00:39:01.255
He told us to stop.

665
00:39:05.926 --> 00:39:07.636
[Rafa] <i>We had a team meeting…</i>

666
00:39:09.597 --> 00:39:11.640
<i>and I decided to go to Indian Wells.</i>

667
00:39:12.224 --> 00:39:14.602
I did. I said.
"I'm going to Indian Wells."

668
00:39:16.020 --> 00:39:18.022
[soft hopeful music playing]

669
00:39:21.525 --> 00:39:24.570
[Rafa] <i>I hadn't set foot</i>
<i>on a hard court in eight months.</i>

670
00:39:25.821 --> 00:39:29.492
And I asked them to put anesthesia
in my knee so I could play.

671
00:39:30.493 --> 00:39:32.328
<i>Otherwise. I couldn't move.</i>

672
00:39:34.747 --> 00:39:36.207
[commentator] <i>That's the shot!</i>

673
00:39:36.290 --> 00:39:38.292
I was playing well. kept playing well.

674
00:39:41.045 --> 00:39:42.963
<i>And I ended up winning the tournament.</i>

675
00:39:43.047 --> 00:39:47.259
[commentator] <i>A record-breaking</i>
<i>22nd ATP Masters 1000!</i>

676
00:39:47.343 --> 00:39:51.097
[Rafa] And. here.
a new season opens up for me.

677
00:39:52.014 --> 00:39:52.932
Just like that.

678
00:39:55.559 --> 00:39:59.814
2013 comes along and he suddenly
starts winning absolutely everything.

679
00:39:59.897 --> 00:40:03.109
[commentator 1] <i>His return</i>
<i>to form has been fantastic.</i>

680
00:40:03.609 --> 00:40:06.362
[commentator 2]
<i>Rafael Nadal is a champion in Barcelona</i>

681
00:40:06.445 --> 00:40:09.281
<i>for an incredible eighth time.</i>

682
00:40:10.366 --> 00:40:12.535
[Rafa] <i>I feel awful.</i>
<i>my knee is hurting a lot.</i>

683
00:40:13.119 --> 00:40:14.829
<i>but it's not the right time to…</i>

684
00:40:17.248 --> 00:40:18.082
to stop.

685
00:40:18.165 --> 00:40:20.084
[crowd cheering]

686
00:40:21.460 --> 00:40:23.921
[Maribel] <i>It's not just the pain</i>
<i>when you play.</i>

687
00:40:24.004 --> 00:40:25.506
<i>but it's also</i>

688
00:40:26.215 --> 00:40:28.384
<i>in your daily life.</i>
<i>like going down the stairs.</i>

689
00:40:29.718 --> 00:40:31.720
[music fades]

690
00:40:32.638 --> 00:40:34.557
I was very worried.

691
00:40:37.143 --> 00:40:41.230
You see someone suffering
and you don't know how to help them.

692
00:40:42.440 --> 00:40:44.817
<i>Of course. in the end.</i>
<i>it makes your heart sink.</i>

693
00:40:46.277 --> 00:40:47.862
[unsettling music playing]

694
00:40:49.071 --> 00:40:51.866
[Rafa] <i>I'm taking a lot</i>
<i>of anti-inflammatories to play.</i>

695
00:40:52.575 --> 00:40:54.368
<i>Voltaren at night…</i>

696
00:40:55.578 --> 00:40:59.957
<i>and an intramuscular Voltaren injection</i>
<i>before every match.</i>

697
00:41:00.708 --> 00:41:02.710
[applause]

698
00:41:05.379 --> 00:41:10.134
[commentator 1] <i>Seventh final</i>
<i>in the seventh event since his return</i>

699
00:41:10.217 --> 00:41:11.635
<i>for the great Spaniard.</i>

700
00:41:17.433 --> 00:41:21.312
It became tough to deal
with the pain he suffered every day.

701
00:41:22.813 --> 00:41:26.025
<i>And to see him take</i>
<i>so many anti-inflammatories</i>

702
00:41:26.108 --> 00:41:29.945
that could be harmful to his health.

703
00:41:30.654 --> 00:41:31.489
[line] Out!

704
00:41:31.572 --> 00:41:34.867
[commentator 2]
<i>Nadal is the maestro in Madrid</i>

705
00:41:34.950 --> 00:41:36.785
<i>for a third time!</i>

706
00:41:37.286 --> 00:41:38.996
I want to thank my whole team.

707
00:41:39.079 --> 00:41:40.080
Without you all.

708
00:41:40.164 --> 00:41:42.666
it would be impossible
to be here again today.

709
00:41:43.959 --> 00:41:45.753
[Maymó] <i>We clashed at times</i>

710
00:41:45.836 --> 00:41:49.215
<i>because I thought he was taking too many.</i>

711
00:41:49.798 --> 00:41:52.218
or that at certain times
it wasn't necessary.

712
00:41:59.058 --> 00:42:01.852
[Rafa] <i>Maymó was against all of it.</i>

713
00:42:02.978 --> 00:42:04.647
Every time I asked about medicine…

714
00:42:07.942 --> 00:42:09.944
I had to make my own decisions.

715
00:42:11.487 --> 00:42:12.905
[Maymó] <i>There came a time when Rafa</i>

716
00:42:12.988 --> 00:42:15.658
<i>started carrying</i>
<i>his own anti-inflammatories.</i>

717
00:42:16.158 --> 00:42:18.035
<i>He got to the point of taking them…</i>

718
00:42:18.744 --> 00:42:20.454
<i>not because he was in pain.</i>

719
00:42:20.996 --> 00:42:23.374
<i>but to prevent the pain from coming again.</i>

720
00:42:23.457 --> 00:42:26.252
[commentator]
<i>His seventh victory here in Rome!</i>

721
00:42:26.335 --> 00:42:29.505
<i>His numbers improve</i>
<i>with each passing victory.</i>

722
00:42:30.589 --> 00:42:32.007
[Rafa] <i>I said. "Okay. whatever."</i>

723
00:42:32.091 --> 00:42:35.928
<i>"I have my medicine and I'll take it</i>
<i>when I think I need to take it."</i>

724
00:42:43.185 --> 00:42:45.980
[announcer] <i>…Rafael Nadal!</i>

725
00:42:47.147 --> 00:42:48.857
[Maribel] <i>Sometimes. winning</i>

726
00:42:50.150 --> 00:42:53.112
gives you a perception of reality

727
00:42:54.113 --> 00:42:55.573
<i> that is not real.</i>

728
00:42:57.741 --> 00:42:59.451
<i>Because your health</i>

729
00:43:00.160 --> 00:43:04.123
<i>is much more important than any success.</i>

730
00:43:04.873 --> 00:43:07.960
[commentator 1] <i>Rafael Nadal</i>
<i>is your champion in Canada!</i>

731
00:43:08.961 --> 00:43:13.048
[commentator 2]
<i>Rafael Nadal wins in Cincinnati!</i>

732
00:43:14.341 --> 00:43:18.929
In fact. I have two small perforations
in my intestines.

733
00:43:19.013 --> 00:43:22.933
Small perforations caused
by so many anti-inflammatories.

734
00:43:24.643 --> 00:43:26.312
{\an8}Gentlemen. just a second.

735
00:43:31.025 --> 00:43:33.277
{\an8}- [interviewer] Do you have cramps?
- [Rafa winces]

736
00:43:38.198 --> 00:43:39.617
[commentator] <i>The US Open final.</i>

737
00:43:39.700 --> 00:43:43.537
<i>World number 1. Novak Djokovic</i>
<i>against number 2. Rafael Nadal.</i>

738
00:43:43.621 --> 00:43:46.415
[commentator 2]
<i>And the match that will determine</i>

739
00:43:46.498 --> 00:43:49.418
<i>the number 1 ranking for the year</i>
<i>is this one.</i>

740
00:43:50.669 --> 00:43:54.089
[Rafa] <i>In my career.</i>
<i>I've had to make decisions about my health</i>

741
00:43:54.173 --> 00:43:57.760
where I was on the verge
of what was right or wrong.

742
00:44:03.599 --> 00:44:06.602
This is where I'm telling you
that it's a thin line.

743
00:44:07.603 --> 00:44:11.023
[commentator 2] <i>We are finally</i>
<i>at match point for the championship.</i>

744
00:44:12.191 --> 00:44:14.985
[Rafa] <i>But I think that.</i>
<i>if I hadn't explored.</i>

745
00:44:15.903 --> 00:44:18.989
I might have ten less Grand Slams.

746
00:44:20.991 --> 00:44:24.578
I'm not saying one or two.
I'm saying ten or twelve.

747
00:44:25.162 --> 00:44:26.830
That's the truth.

748
00:44:27.456 --> 00:44:29.458
[music builds]

749
00:44:30.542 --> 00:44:35.339
[commentator] <i>Rafa Nadal has won</i>
<i>the US Open for a second time!</i>

750
00:44:35.422 --> 00:44:37.424
[emotional music playing]

751
00:44:39.760 --> 00:44:41.929
[reporter] <i>Rafa Nadal</i>
<i>is the best in the world again.</i>

752
00:44:42.012 --> 00:44:44.598
<i>He has managed to dethrone Novak Djokovic.</i>

753
00:44:44.682 --> 00:44:47.393
[reporter 2]
<i>A position he hadn't held since 2011.</i>

754
00:44:47.476 --> 00:44:50.062
<i>Rafa Nadal. number 1 in the world.</i>

755
00:44:57.778 --> 00:44:59.738
{\an8}[Moyá] <i>He's a competitor…</i>

756
00:45:00.781 --> 00:45:02.366
{\an8}<i>An addict to competition.</i>

757
00:45:02.866 --> 00:45:04.118
{\an8}<i>That's not easy. </i>[laughs]

758
00:45:07.371 --> 00:45:12.042
Ladies and gentlemen.
your US Open champion. Rafael Nadal.

759
00:45:12.126 --> 00:45:14.378
[Moyá] <i>That adrenaline</i>
<i>that you have on the court.</i>

760
00:45:14.461 --> 00:45:16.547
<i>that feeling you have</i>
<i>when you are competing</i>

761
00:45:16.630 --> 00:45:20.467
<i>in front of 20.000 people</i>
<i>in the crowd supporting you…</i>

762
00:45:20.968 --> 00:45:23.762
[crowd chanting] Rafa! Rafa!

763
00:45:23.846 --> 00:45:25.097
[Moyá] <i>It's an addiction.</i>

764
00:45:25.931 --> 00:45:29.727
- [rapturous cheering]
- [emotional music continues]

765
00:45:49.496 --> 00:45:51.123
[music fades]

766
00:45:51.206 --> 00:45:52.416
[Rafa] I can feel it a little.

767
00:45:52.499 --> 00:45:55.085
I can feel the whole thing
is a little more swollen.

768
00:45:55.169 --> 00:45:56.211
[Ruiz-Cotorro] Let me see.

769
00:45:57.171 --> 00:45:58.213
Bend it.

770
00:45:59.465 --> 00:46:00.924
Over here. Move it.

771
00:46:05.679 --> 00:46:08.390
[Rafa] I think it's around here.
Up and down. around this area.

772
00:46:08.474 --> 00:46:10.267
[man] Okay. And it's deep. right?

773
00:46:10.768 --> 00:46:14.313
[Rafa] I have a question.
There's nothing we can do about it. right?

774
00:46:14.396 --> 00:46:17.232
- Well. we have to do what we're doing.
- Okay. perfect.

775
00:46:17.816 --> 00:46:19.401
That pain… I'm not worried about it.

776
00:46:22.654 --> 00:46:25.073
[ominous music playing]

777
00:46:26.074 --> 00:46:28.619
[journalist]
I just wondered. Rafa. how hard it is

778
00:46:28.702 --> 00:46:31.497
kind of managing your body
in these matches.

779
00:46:31.580 --> 00:46:33.540
knowing that you need to think about.

780
00:46:33.624 --> 00:46:36.835
or making sure
that you're not hurting yourself.

781
00:46:38.420 --> 00:46:41.215
[Rafa] <i>I have some. some issues.</i>

782
00:46:42.049 --> 00:46:44.718
<i>But that's it.</i>
<i>I just accept the situation.</i>

783
00:46:44.802 --> 00:46:46.595
[resolute music playing]

784
00:46:46.678 --> 00:46:48.555
[Rafa] <i>There arrives a moment today</i>

785
00:46:48.639 --> 00:46:51.809
<i>that I need to try to play at my 100%.</i>

786
00:46:53.602 --> 00:46:56.605
<i>I have Roland-Garros</i>
<i>in two weeks and a half.</i>

787
00:46:56.688 --> 00:46:58.857
<i>I need to push my body to the limit.</i>

788
00:46:58.941 --> 00:47:01.944
<i>And if something happens.</i>
<i>something happens.</i>

789
00:47:03.445 --> 00:47:05.447
[action music playing]

790
00:47:05.531 --> 00:47:08.200
[commentator 1] <i>Second round action</i>
<i>continues here in Rome.</i>

791
00:47:08.700 --> 00:47:10.828
<i>It is the number 7 seed. Hubert Hurkacz.</i>

792
00:47:10.911 --> 00:47:12.663
<i>up against Rafa Nadal.</i>

793
00:47:12.746 --> 00:47:15.332
<i>- Who's your favorite?</i>
<i>- </i>[commentator 2] <i>I think Nadal.</i>

794
00:47:15.833 --> 00:47:17.960
[commentator 3]
<i>Rafa and Stanislas Wawrinka</i>

795
00:47:18.043 --> 00:47:19.628
<i>make their way onto Rod Laver Arena.</i>

796
00:47:19.711 --> 00:47:23.215
<i>Gosh! You look at recent history.</i>
<i>you look at head-to-heads.</i>

797
00:47:23.298 --> 00:47:25.259
<i>it all favors the world number 1.</i>

798
00:47:25.342 --> 00:47:26.552
[commentator 1] <i>A packed house.</i>

799
00:47:26.635 --> 00:47:30.639
<i>Eager to see how Rafa Nadal</i>
<i>will get on in his latest test.</i>

800
00:47:32.391 --> 00:47:34.184
[Rafa] <i>2014 begins.</i>

801
00:47:34.268 --> 00:47:35.686
<i>I was number 1.</i>

802
00:47:36.228 --> 00:47:38.438
And I was willing to. well…

803
00:47:39.022 --> 00:47:41.900
<i>go to the limit of my possibilities.</i>

804
00:47:47.906 --> 00:47:49.658
[commentator 2] <i>Rafa in full control.</i>

805
00:47:53.579 --> 00:47:54.872
<i>Oh. what a start!</i>

806
00:47:57.416 --> 00:48:00.294
[commentator 1] <i>He's going all out today.</i>
<i>from what we're seeing so far.</i>

807
00:48:08.135 --> 00:48:09.636
[Rafa] <i>And all of a sudden…</i>

808
00:48:10.345 --> 00:48:11.346
<i>Boom.</i>

809
00:48:12.014 --> 00:48:14.808
<i>I felt pain in my back.</i>

810
00:48:16.018 --> 00:48:18.020
<i>And I felt that I couldn't.</i>

811
00:48:18.562 --> 00:48:19.396
<i>I couldn't.</i>

812
00:48:21.231 --> 00:48:22.316
I just couldn't.

813
00:48:23.358 --> 00:48:25.360
[ethereal suspenseful music playing]

814
00:48:28.822 --> 00:48:31.283
[commentator] <i>Oof! Risky business!</i>

815
00:48:32.743 --> 00:48:36.914
His foot is bothering him.
Did you see that? Couldn't even move.

816
00:48:41.627 --> 00:48:43.462
[commentator]
<i>He's looking up at Uncle Toni.</i>

817
00:48:43.962 --> 00:48:46.423
<i>It's not a look of</i>
<i>"I've got this figured out."</i>

818
00:48:46.506 --> 00:48:48.634
<i> It's a look of genuine concern.</i>

819
00:48:55.682 --> 00:48:57.559
[commentator 2]
<i>They'll put him on the ground.</i>

820
00:49:00.270 --> 00:49:03.607
<i>If it's the back.</i>
<i>he would have taken some painkillers.</i>

821
00:49:04.441 --> 00:49:05.442
<i> He's done.</i>

822
00:49:07.235 --> 00:49:09.029
[Maymó] <i>Injuries. the stress.</i>

823
00:49:10.489 --> 00:49:13.492
always pushing your body
and mind to the limit…

824
00:49:15.118 --> 00:49:19.373
<i>Then came the moment</i>
<i>when all that started to bring…</i>

825
00:49:19.957 --> 00:49:21.416
<i> consequences.</i>

826
00:49:24.586 --> 00:49:26.380
Come. Rafael. come on!

827
00:49:26.463 --> 00:49:29.383
Come on. reset! Go!
Let's start again. go! Come on!

828
00:49:29.967 --> 00:49:31.051
Believe it. man!

829
00:49:33.971 --> 00:49:35.597
[commentator] <i>A little clumsy from Nadal.</i>

830
00:49:39.017 --> 00:49:41.645
[commentator 2]
<i>That's a couple that Nadal's missed.</i>

831
00:49:41.728 --> 00:49:44.731
[commentator 3] <i>This is the look of a man</i>
<i>who might not see the finish line</i>

832
00:49:44.815 --> 00:49:46.233
<i>the way he wanted to.</i>

833
00:49:49.069 --> 00:49:50.070
[crowd exclaims]

834
00:49:50.153 --> 00:49:51.321
[applause]

835
00:49:51.405 --> 00:49:54.491
[commentator]
<i>It is indeed victory for Hubie Hurkacz</i>

836
00:49:54.574 --> 00:49:57.536
<i>as Rafa says goodbye to Rome.</i>

837
00:49:59.830 --> 00:50:00.914
[applause fades]

838
00:50:04.001 --> 00:50:06.670
[PA system alert]

839
00:50:06.753 --> 00:50:09.631
[voice on PA] <i>Attention. players.</i>
<i>this is a match call.</i>

840
00:50:10.215 --> 00:50:13.969
<i>Please go to the meeting point</i>
<i>to be escorted to your court.</i>

841
00:50:14.469 --> 00:50:16.513
[Moyá] Don't make any decisions now. okay.

842
00:50:17.764 --> 00:50:18.932
Whatever you want to do.

843
00:50:19.016 --> 00:50:21.351
there'll be time in a few days to…

844
00:50:21.893 --> 00:50:23.645
to do whatever it is. okay?

845
00:50:28.942 --> 00:50:30.944
[somber music playing]

846
00:50:35.032 --> 00:50:38.785
[Rafa] <i>I've been fighting</i>
<i>against my body for many years.</i>

847
00:50:41.580 --> 00:50:43.957
<i>Always with the highest demand.</i>

848
00:50:46.376 --> 00:50:50.839
<i>And this is mentally draining.</i>
<i>It's truly exhausting.</i>

849
00:50:52.924 --> 00:50:56.428
<i>And there comes a time</i>
<i>when it all collapses.</i>

850
00:51:01.141 --> 00:51:05.020
- [indistinct chatter]
- [ball hitting racket]

851
00:51:07.105 --> 00:51:09.357
You guys don't know. truly. huh?

852
00:51:10.859 --> 00:51:13.528
Now with my… Honestly. man.

853
00:51:14.237 --> 00:51:16.031
I am incredibly exhausted.

854
00:51:16.615 --> 00:51:18.909
It's a constant. man.

855
00:51:19.576 --> 00:51:23.205
I'm the most punctured player
in the history of our sport.

856
00:51:27.375 --> 00:51:29.294
[Moyá] I know it's hard.
but we keep going.

857
00:51:30.462 --> 00:51:31.671
There's no option.

858
00:51:32.672 --> 00:51:35.217
You can also go like this.

859
00:51:37.552 --> 00:51:40.013
You put a little nail up here…

860
00:51:40.097 --> 00:51:41.348
[Moyá] I don't agree.

861
00:51:42.891 --> 00:51:43.725
And it's over.

862
00:51:44.851 --> 00:51:46.186
The little nail can wait.

863
00:51:50.982 --> 00:51:52.984
[somber music continues]

864
00:52:06.998 --> 00:52:09.042
[Rafa] I mean. what tennis gives me…

865
00:52:10.752 --> 00:52:12.963
I mean. what it gives me today.

866
00:52:13.046 --> 00:52:16.091
it takes away much more than it gives me.

867
00:52:17.801 --> 00:52:19.636
- [María] Well. right now.
- You know?

868
00:52:19.719 --> 00:52:24.057
I mean. in terms of personal fulfillment.

869
00:52:24.141 --> 00:52:25.642
fun. suffering…

870
00:52:25.725 --> 00:52:30.355
Right now. it takes away
much more than it gives me.

871
00:52:32.899 --> 00:52:34.776
[María] Another life is waiting for you.

872
00:52:45.287 --> 00:52:46.663
[music fades]

873
00:52:48.165 --> 00:52:50.167
[serene music playing]

874
00:54:20.799 --> 00:54:22.801
[dynamic serene music playing]

875
00:57:14.222 --> 00:57:16.224
[music fades]
